- Uses proper `name`, `short_name`, `start_url`, `scope`, `display`, colors, and language per current PWA guidelines.[1][2][3]
- Includes multiple `icons` with `purpose: "any maskable"` for adaptive, wave‑themed icons on Android and other platforms.[1][4][5]
- Adds rich `screenshots`, `categories`, and `shortcuts` so app stores and OS surfaces can show pretty previews and quick actions that match your “waves and lines” visual identity.[6][7][8][9]

